cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CG. 

This paper deals with the decoding of LDPC codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses techniques from the study of limitations of LP/SDP hierarchies for Max-CSPs (cs.DS), and the construction of special distributions and subgroups (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of balanced pairwise independent distributions, which is a topic in combinatorics (cs.DM) and the stretching and collapsing technique used in the proofs may be related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
